---
import StoryLayout from '../../layouts/StoryLayout.astro';
import stories from '../../data/stories.json';

const story = stories.find(s => s.slug === 'arup-deepfake-cfo')!;
---

<style is:global>
  .arup-msg-mockup { max-width: 420px; margin: 2rem auto; background: var(--surface); border: 1px solid var(--border); border-radius: 1rem; overflow: hidden; font-family: -apple-system, 'Segoe UI', sans-serif; }
  .arup-msg-header { padding: 0.75rem 1.25rem; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border); display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 0.75rem; }
  .arup-msg-avatar { width: 36px; height: 36px; border-radius: 50%; background: var(--border); display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center; font-size: 0.85rem; color: var(--muted); font-weight: 700; }
  .arup-msg-sender { flex: 1; }
  .arup-msg-name { font-size: 0.88rem; font-weight: 700; color: var(--text); }
  .arup-msg-role { font-size: 0.72rem; color: var(--muted); }
  .arup-msg-body { padding: 1.25rem; font-size: 0.9rem; line-height: 1.65; color: #c0c0c0; }
  .arup-msg-body p { margin: 0 0 0.75rem; }
  .arup-msg-body p:last-child { margin-bottom: 0; }
  .arup-msg-confidential { color: var(--text); font-weight: 600; font-style: italic; }
  .arup-msg-footer { padding: 0.65rem 1.25rem; border-top: 1px solid var(--border); display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 0.5rem; font-size: 0.72rem; }
  .arup-msg-flag-icon { width: 8px; height: 8px; border-radius: 50%; background: var(--story); flex-shrink: 0; }
  .arup-msg-flag-text { color: var(--story); letter-spacing: 0.05em; text-transform: uppercase; font-weight: 600; }
  .arup-msg-context { font-size: 0.78rem; color: var(--muted); text-align: center; margin: 0.75rem auto 0; max-width: 420px; font-style: italic; }

  .arup-call-mockup { max-width: 560px; margin: 2rem auto; background: #111; border: 1px solid var(--border); border-radius: 1rem; overflow: hidden; }
  .arup-call-bar { padding: 0.6rem 1.25rem; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border); display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: space-between; font-size: 0.72rem; color: var(--muted); }
  .arup-call-bar-left { display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 0.5rem; }
  .arup-call-rec { width: 8px; height: 8px; border-radius: 50%; background: var(--accent); animation: arup-blink 1.5s infinite; }
  @keyframes arup-blink { 0%, 100% { opacity: 1; } 50% { opacity: 0.3; } }
  .arup-call-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr 1fr; gap: 4px; padding: 4px; }
  .arup-call-tile { aspect-ratio: 4 / 3; border-radius: 0.5rem; display: flex; flex-direction: column; align-items: center; justify-content: center; position: relative; overflow: hidden; }
  .arup-call-tile-fake { background: linear-gradient(145deg, #1a1a2e 0%, #16213e 100%); border: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.04); }
  .arup-call-tile-real { background: linear-gradient(145deg, #1a2e1a 0%, #162e21 100%); border: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.08); }
  .arup-call-tile-label { font-size: 0.72rem; font-weight: 600; color: rgba(255,255,255,0.7); margin-bottom: 0.2rem; }
  .arup-call-tile-role { font-size: 0.62rem; color: rgba(255,255,255,0.55); letter-spacing: 0.05em; text-transform: uppercase; }
  .arup-call-tile-icon { font-size: 1.4rem; margin-bottom: 0.4rem; opacity: 0.6; }
  .arup-call-tile-scanline { position: absolute; inset: 0; background: repeating-linear-gradient(0deg, transparent 0px, transparent 3px, rgba(255,255,255,0.015) 3px, rgba(255,255,255,0.015) 4px); pointer-events: none; }
  .arup-call-tile-fake .arup-call-tile-scanline { background: repeating-linear-gradient(0deg, transparent 0px, transparent 3px, rgba(110,168,201,0.04) 3px, rgba(110,168,201,0.04) 4px); }
  .arup-call-footer { padding: 0.75rem 1.25rem; border-top: 1px solid var(--border); text-align: center; }
  .arup-call-quote { font-size: 0.82rem; font-style: italic; color: var(--muted); line-height: 1.5; }
  .arup-call-quote cite { display: block; font-size: 0.72rem; margin-top: 0.3rem; color: var(--story); font-style: normal; letter-spacing: 0.05em; }
  .arup-call-context { font-size: 0.78rem; color: var(--muted); text-align: center; margin: 0.75rem auto 0; max-width: 560px; font-style: italic; }
  @media (max-width: 500px) { .arup-call-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; } }
  @media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce) { .arup-call-rec { animation: none; } }

  .arup-ledger { max-width: 560px; margin: 2rem auto; background: var(--bg); border: 1px solid var(--border); border-radius: 0.75rem; overflow: hidden; font-family: 'Courier New', monospace; }
  .arup-ledger-header { padding: 0.65rem 1rem; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border); font-size: 0.68rem; color: var(--muted); letter-spacing: 0.1em; text-transform: uppercase; display: flex; justify-content: space-between; }
  .arup-ledger-body { max-height: 360px; overflow-y: auto; }
  .arup-ledger-row { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 36px 80px 1fr 100px; gap: 0.5rem; padding: 0.4rem 1rem; font-size: 0.78rem; border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.03); color: #a0a0a0; align-items: center; }
  .arup-ledger-row:nth-child(even) { background: rgba(255,255,255,0.015); }
  .arup-ledger-num { color: var(--muted); font-size: 0.7rem; }
  .arup-ledger-date { color: var(--muted); }
  .arup-ledger-acct { color: rgba(255,255,255,0.5); }
  .arup-ledger-amt { text-align: right; color: var(--story); font-weight: 600; }
  .arup-ledger-total { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 100px; gap: 0.5rem; padding: 0.75rem 1rem; border-top: 2px solid var(--border); font-size: 0.85rem; font-weight: 900; }
  .arup-ledger-total-label { color: var(--text); }
  .arup-ledger-total-amt { text-align: right; color: var(--accent); }
  .arup-ledger-footer { padding: 0.65rem 1rem; border-top: 1px solid var(--border); font-size: 0.72rem; color: var(--muted); font-family: -apple-system, 'Segoe UI', sans-serif; font-style: italic; }
  .arup-ledger-footer strong { color: var(--accent); font-style: normal; }
  .arup-ledger-context { font-size: 0.78rem; color: var(--muted); text-align: center; margin: 0.75rem auto 0; max-width: 560px; font-style: italic; }
  @media (max-width: 500px) {
    .arup-ledger-row { grid-template-columns: 28px 64px 1fr 80px; font-size: 0.7rem; }
    .arup-ledger-total { font-size: 0.78rem; }
  }

  .phantom-wrap { width: 100%; margin: 0; line-height: 0; }
  .arup-deepfake-cfo-canvas { display: block; width: 100%; height: 380px; background: var(--bg); }
</style>

<StoryLayout story={story}>
  <div class="container">
    <section class="section" id="context">
      <h2><span class="num">01 — The Right Instinct</span>Context</h2>
      <p>In mid-January 2024, a finance worker at the Hong Kong office of Arup — the London-headquartered engineering firm behind the Sydney Opera House and Beijing's Bird's Nest — received a message from the company's UK-based chief financial officer. The CFO requested a confidential transaction. The message carried the right tone, the right corporate language, the right sense of authority. It also carried a demand for secrecy: the matter was to remain confidential until further notice.</p>

      <div class="arup-msg-mockup">
        <div class="arup-msg-header">
          <div class="arup-msg-avatar">CFO</div>
          <div class="arup-msg-sender">
            <div class="arup-msg-name">CFO — UK Head Office</div>
            <div class="arup-msg-role">Global Finance, London</div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="arup-msg-body">
          <p>I need you to carry out a series of transactions on behalf of the company. The details will follow shortly. <span class="arup-msg-confidential">This must remain confidential until further notice.</span></p>
          <p>Please treat this as priority and do not discuss with local colleagues at this stage.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="arup-msg-footer">
          <span class="arup-msg-flag-icon" aria-hidden="true"></span>
          <span class="arup-msg-flag-text">Employee flagged as suspicious</span>
        </div>
      </div>
      <p class="arup-msg-context">Reconstructed from police descriptions. The employee suspected phishing and sought verification.</p>

      <p>The employee did not comply. He suspected phishing. This was the correct instinct. Corporate fraud-prevention training across nearly every multinational follows the same script — if you receive an unusual financial request from a senior executive, especially one demanding secrecy, do not act on it. Verify first.</p>
      <p>He got on a video call to verify.</p>
      <p>This is where every security protocol in the world assumed the process would catch the fraud. A voice call is good. A video call is better. You see the face, you hear the voice, you confirm the person is who they claim to be. The employee joined a video conference expecting to see his CFO and several colleagues. He saw them. They looked right. They sounded right.</p>
      <p>According to Acting Senior Superintendent Baron Chan Shun-ching of the Hong Kong Police, previous deepfake fraud cases in the territory had involved one-on-one video calls. This call was different in scale — multiple recognized colleagues appeared simultaneously — but not in kind. It looked like a normal meeting.</p>
    </section>

    <div class="phantom-wrap">
      <canvas class="arup-deepfake-cfo-canvas" aria-hidden="true"></canvas>
    </div>
    <p class="canvas-note"><strong>The Verification</strong> — Five nodes pulse in an arc, performing liveness. A lone particle approaches, cautious at first, then trusting. Stillness settles. One by one, each node flickers with interference and dissolves into an empty ring. The particle stands alone in darkness. The nodes reform. The cycle restarts.</p>

    <section class="section" id="event">
      <h2><span class="num">02 — Everyone Was Fake</span>What Happened</h2>
      <p>Every person the employee saw on that call was an AI-generated deepfake.</p>
      <p>The CFO was fake. The colleagues were fake. According to Baron Chan, "everyone [he saw] was fake." The police later determined that the scammers had downloaded publicly available video and audio of the impersonation targets — footage from YouTube, online conferences, and public-facing company meetings — and used AI to generate synchronized visual and audio deepfakes.</p>
      <p>Baron Chan described the method to RTHK: "I believe the fraudster downloaded videos in advance and then used artificial intelligence to add fake voices." According to China Daily Hong Kong, the deepfakes used pre-recorded voices and the scammers deliberately avoided extended conversation — a technique consistent with limiting the window for detection.</p>

